{"_id":"0BhyOQ8r0D3yhQmF","name":"[10] Villein (Krisi of Clan Drebor)","content":"<p>Krisi is young and he and his wife did not have any children when Lord Akitt arrived. He is supporting two orphaned nephews (14 and 17), though it is not too much of a burden because they are old enough to work. He has enough land to feed his own family and in his role as clan head, he shares his surplus with the less fortunate members of his clan. He works hard to keep peace in the village, fearing that if the villagers cause trouble, it will only make things worse. He will be one of the most useful supporters of any new bailiff.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":2000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"1zwlm9bz1pIGkDOO","name":"[F] Bridge","content":"<h2>Bridge</h2><p>The bridge framework is still strong, but several of the planks on the roadway are rotten and need to be replaced. The lane to the south-west is just five years old. It leads to the King’s forest where most of the logging took place. It is heavily rutted.</p>\n","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"2hw71NCQHgis5kKm","name":"[33] Cottar (Endaen of Clan Heryla)","content":"<p>Endaen has two teenage boys and a girl (11). His wife died three years ago and the children are being cared for by his elderly spinster aunt. He works for hi cousin, Harquey (@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.Xqwk8LbewxpPnMhQ]{[19] Villein-Herder (Harquey of Clan Heryla)}), the village herder. He is also an accomplished poacher. He has a short bow and arrows hidden in the woods.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":6600000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"3AEzEYRVAIMKKJHd","name":"[M2] Gatehouse and guard room","content":"<h2>Gatehouse and guard room</h2><p>A pile of half-burned timbers and rubble mark the previous location of a small timber-frame building. It was the home of Akitt’s two mercenaries, Kenric and Hedin, until they left the fire unattended while drunk and it caught fire. After that, they lived in the main hall. The gatehouse was never rebuilt or even cleaned up.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Sir Peart Tanush, Temporary Bailiff","content":"<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">Sir Peart Tanush is the deputy to the Earl of Neph’s Steward. In this role, he is responsible for making assessments on manors for their feudal payments. A moderately skilled knight, he has a razor sharp mind and is extremely well educated. He is literate in three languages, a talented mathematician and has an excellent eye for value (especially the value of a manor, crops and livestock). This is his first visit to Charmic since Lord Akitt took over the manor from Clan Morfan. He is completely appalled. When he inspected the manor just before the previous bailiffs left it was in excellent shape and very capable of supporting a knight with a large household. He believes it will take at least three years to put things right. If PCs make friends with Sir Peart he can be a powerful ally in the Earl’s court, especially when the new bailiff has to negotiate future feudal payments.</span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZHcuaOyz810x9hQU":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.WiQtn4JRu1wi8mcO"}},"_id":"3cza1PzefasoghBW"}
{"_id":"3hV5vBR4O0dZMZXW","name":"[29] Villein–Reeve (Jodion of Clan Drebor)","content":"<p>Shortly after Akitt arrived, Jodion took the opportunity to make himself useful to the new lord by reporting other villagers who were shirking their duty. Soon, he became Akitt’s eyes and ears in the village. In 717, the bailiff had had enough of Witol’s whining about fief maintenance and crops, and sacked him. Jodion was the natural choice to replace him. He agreed to what ever the lord said and drove his fellow villagers without mercy. He and his wife, sister, son and two daughters live very comfortably. Secretly, his son despises Jodion and was planning to kill Akitt with a dagger he stole from his father, but the bailiff ran before he had a chance. The boy plans to flee Charmic and shame his father. He will follow any bounty hunters who come to the village and beg to join the hunt for Akitt and his men.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":5800000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"5e1vGSTIi3tQO1Vr","name":"[7] Half-Villein (Maras of Clan Drebor)","content":"<p>Maras’ family is too large for the amount of land he works. With only eighteen acres, he must try and feed himself, two brothers, sister-in-law, nephew and niece. His wife and two young children died last winter. He rarely talks except to ask for another beer.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"81NwzVzNkBAT9YJn","name":"[M7] Kitchen","content":"<h2>Kitchen</h2><p>Built separately from the main hall in event of fire, this building is home to the two of the servants Akitt kept on after he assumed control of the fief. The cook is an older woman and was much abused by the men-at-arms. She is quite willing to tell everything she knows to anyone who will listen. The domestic is a young girl, once quite pretty; she cleaned, washed and served the lord and his men. In return for her hard work, she was raped regularly. She is now mute, though some tender loving care from another woman might get her to talk. After raping her, during what he felt was a sensitive moment, Akitt once told her his uncle lives near Thay.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"8wmGyg37MWU3QCHO","name":"[G] Track to Zernhol Manor","content":"<h2>Track to Zernhol Manor</h2><p>This narrow and rutted track eventually leads to the next manor. Few use it as the road is plagued by wolves that have grown bold indeed over the last few years.</p>\n","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9SQgckgf2zILvUwo","name":"[3] Metalsmith (Varyl of Clan Drengen)","content":"<p>Size: 4 Quality: ★★★ Price: Average</p>\n<p>Varyl is particularly vulnerable. During the good times under Clan Morfan, he invested heavily, borrowing from a usurer to buy this franchise and taking on a journeyman and two apprentices in expectations of growth on the manor. He also has a wife, three children (12, 11 and 8), his mother-in-law and his aunt to support. Akitt knew this, and used it to keep him at the verge of financial ruin in order to control him. Varyl has severe ulcers and drinks heavily.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":600000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9cJCnNVapB8RMvOW","name":"[M4] Kennel","content":"<h2>Kennel</h2><p>This shelter once housed a dog-boy and several hunting dogs. Since the departure of Clan Morfan, it has stood empty. It is now home to a particularly territorial badger.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":800000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9p3cZvgzVXEDZJzU","name":"[31] Cottar (Arath of Clan Narad)","content":"<p>An outsider with a wife, teenage son and elderly parents to support, Arath had no choice but to throw his lot in with Akitt. He bullied the other villagers and did what he was told. Unlike some others, he never revelled in his task and tried to moderate the punishments meted out. Unfortunately, the villagers have lumped him in with the other “enforcers” and now he fears for the safety of his family. He will try and ingratiate himself wi anyone in power.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":6200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"9u9m9qqsy1HNjWkr","name":"_Overview","content":"<p><img style=\"width:100%\" src=\"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/charmic-village.webp\" /></p>\n<p>Charmic is a \"Location Module\"; it is designed to depict the Charmic manor and village located in Kirsta Hundred, Nephshire, kingdom of Kaldor, on the island of Hârn in the <a href=\"https://columbiagames.com/harnworld/\">HârnWorld fantasy setting</a>; however, this manor and village could be adapted to exist anywhere in any fantasy setting.</p>\n<p>This module is based on the \"<a href=\"https://www.lythia.com/harnworld/settlements/charmic/\">Charmic</a>\" fanon; please see @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.TUYZDcoAZOzGRO5X]{Credits} for more information.</p>\n<p>This manor is held directly by the Earl of Neph and managed by a bailiff; until recently his bastard brother Akitt. It is a relatively new manor with huge potential, and grew very prosperous under its original bailiff. But in recent years, it has become a dark and dangerous place.</p>\n<p>This module details all of the households, including interior plans of the manor; plus illustrations by Richard Luschek.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Using this module with Non-HârnMaster systems</h2>\n<p>This entire module is system-agnostic.  See the section below on NPCs for details about the residents; these details may be used to generate appropriate statistics for your game system.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Using the Scenes</h2>\n<p>A number of scenes are provided representing maps. These scenes depict both internal and external areas; internal areas are generally set at a 5-foot grid spacing, while exterior areas use much larger scaling. The following subsections describe some common elements of these scenes.</p>\n<h3>Map Notes</h3>\n<p>The scenes make extensive use of Map Notes to provide detailed description of important areas in the scenes. To view these map notes, click on the \"bookmark icon\" in the canvas toolbar. Map notes are not visible to players, only to the GM.</p>\n<h3>Text and Markings</h3>\n<p>In various areas text and or markings have been provided in the scenes to assist the GM. Generally this information is set to only be visible to the GM.</p>\n<h3>Stairs</h3>\n<p>Some stairs may have an arrow indicating the direction the stairs descend. When present these arrows are visible to all players.</p>\n<h3>Lighting</h3>\n<p>To control ambient lighting, use the \"darkness\" setting for the scene.</p>\n<p>All scenes have been setup with Unrestricted Vision Range enabled, with a Vision Limitation Threshold set to 0.7. This allows all areas of the scene to be lit during the day, but vision is limited and lights are required at night.</p>\n<p>Internal lamps and candle lights have been placed in indoor areas. These lights have been set to enable when the \"darkness\" setting is ≥ 0.2, that is, just after things start becoming dim.</p>\n<p>Hârn has a cool climate, so all fireplaces and braziers are constantly lit.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Recommended Modules</h2>\n<p>The following modules, although not required, are highly recommended to enhance this module:</p>\n<p><strong>Compendium Folders: </strong>Due to the large number of journal entries in this module, these journal entries have been organized into sub-folders using Compendium Folders.  If Compendium Folders is not used, these will all show up as a single long list of Journal Entries in the compendium.  As long as you follow the links starting with the _Overview journal entry, it should not be necessary to navigate the compendium, but if you want to navigate through the Journal Entries yourself, having Compendium Folders will greately simplify this task.</p>\n<p><strong>Backgroundless Pins:</strong> The note icons all have a dark grey background; with this module, that background disappears.  This may increase your enjoyment of the maps.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Background Information</h2>\n<p>For historical, political, and recent events, see @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.ZmEliTNa7r9v7mPd]{Settlement Overview}.</p>\n<p>For a sketch of life in Charmic village, see @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.xwcD6712oKdxZPT9]{Charmic Village}.</p>\n<p>For HarnManor data on the settlement, see @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.Oe8B1ewYk78UCMiP]{Settlement Data}.</p>\n<p>There is far more to Koman of Torlis than anyone guesses: for details, see @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.owFvdvrbdDQzJT6N]{[38] Villein (Koman of Clan Torlis)}.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Local Map</h2>\n<p>The following locations are all depicted in the Charmic Village scene.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.GafDnQ5j88ctMsnK]{[A] Manor House}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.mmJU8YZN4gJtuprU]{[B] Manor Wood Lot}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.aNx2DdHeSk7wAnQu]{[C] Village Common}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.HgD6rUwomnijjcvw]{[D] Peonian Shrine}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.RGrnBjT8Z2QJqLM4]{[E] Meadowland}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.1zwlm9bz1pIGkDOO]{[F] Bridge}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.8wmGyg37MWU3QCHO]{[G] Track to Zernhol Manor}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.nYObOPamI3gB9jAa]{[H] Road to Umbrea Manor}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.w2K6gQyVJHXFb6To]{[I] Timberwright's Yard}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.rqNEKzRTdp8wiP6i]{[J] Demesne Farm}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Timberwright's Yard</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.m2FprhjCX1XAG2Cq]{[T1] Tool Shed}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.xgZPCm7hGQ4YKzG2]{[T2] Timberwright’s House}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.hUrOCmU9nQFTp7V9]{[T3] Drying House}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.trNFqgeEGoXbgoUR]{[T4] Sawpit}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.rmX7nKyb5JQrRq5L]{[T5] Sawdust Pile}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>Manor House</h2>\n<p><strong>Bailiff:</strong> @Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.3cza1PzefasoghBW]{Sir Peart Tanush, Temporary Bailiff}</p>\n<h3>Manor Servants</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">There are currently only three servants at the manor: the cook, one domestic (see [M7]) and a stable boy (see [M5]). Clan Morfan supported twelve plus three men-at-arms. The previous chamberlain, Adilan of Morad, was a free man and was so disgusted by what he saw, he left Akitt’s service shortly after the bailiff arrived. He settled in Gardiren. He is well known to the people of Charmic and could do a great deal to help set things to right. The other domestics were fired by Lord Akitt for being too expensive. Most of them still live in the village. They would be more than happy to return to their old jobs, if they could be convince the new lord is better than the old one (not a difficult task, especially if the new bailiff hired Adilan as his chamberlain).</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>TBD</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>NPCs</h2>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width:3em\">Loc</th>\n<th style=\"width:10em\">Name</th>\n<th>Journal</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manor</td>\n<td>Sir Peart Tanush</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.3cza1PzefasoghBW]{Sir Peart Tanush, Temporary Bailiff}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Girn of Valada</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.c7AbapHmTgtRfjXX]{[1] Cottar (Girn of Clan Valada)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Eld of Kralis</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.MoKlNWRylxzuwJQE]{[2] Villein (Eld of Clan Kralis)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Varyl of Drengen</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.9SQgckgf2zILvUwo]{[3] Metalsmith (Varyl of Clan Drengen)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Umis of Kralis</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.xTWzCyUuF064AGCm]{[4] Half-Villein (Umis of Clan Kralis)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Barane of Heryla</td>\n<td>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.v27HZgZo5lrPxZar]{[5] Half-Villein (Barane of Clan Heryla)}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr