{"_id":"AKFlr4iK03rgCHqO","name":"[M3] Equipment Shed","content":"<h2>Equipment Shed</h2><p>The only things in this building are a single cart with a broken wheel and some rather motheaten tack. The thatched roof has come loose on the right rear corner and rain has leaked in.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":600000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"CF4cfdiNQG9lD1v1","name":"[24] Glebe (Father Perras)","content":"<p><img style=\"width:35%;float:left;margin-right:5px\" src=\"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/father-perras.webp\" /></p>\n<p>For five years, Father Perras preached the gospel of Peoni: Everyone has their station; we must endure; Peoni will send the Earl. In the end, he was forced to take matters into his own hands after he presided over the burial of six children in just one week. He is working closely with Sir Peart and praying hard that the Earl will send a good bailiff to lead them. His support is vital to ruling the manor.</p>\n<p>The village glebe is large, a result of generous support from Clan Morfan over many years. It includes an orchard with apple trees and a large chapel. The priest lives in a small complex of buildings behind the chapel. They include a small tithe barn (completely empty), a pig sty (vacant for three years) and a humble house for Father Perras (built by the parishioners).</p>\n<p>Besides the orchard, there is a large stand of beech nut trees that predate the village. They were left uncut when the village was founded. By tradition, the nuts are collected and shared by the whole community. When he had a pig, Father Perras used to let her forage in the little stand of trees. The area was also a popular playground for the children of the village before the famine and cold winters took most of their lives. It is now deserted and has an eerie, foreboding feeling.</p>\n<p>Between the woods and the road is the village cemetery, much fuller than it was only five years ago. Dozens of mounds with little piles of stones or crude stick markers mark fresh graves. It is all the villagers can afford. The villagers avoid the graveyard by night. People talk of seeing two ghostly figures, a boy and a girl, walking hand in hand through the cemetery. It is rumoured to be the children of Virisla (@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.nRup6IVmzYteGl7e]{[12] Half-Villein (Virisla of Clan Heryla)}) who the residents believe strangled his children in their sleep.</p>","img":"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/father-perras.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":4800000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"FnaFRQ23UuITTsSO","name":"[36] Half-Villein (Raena of Clan Kralis)","content":"<p>Raena depends heavily on Arge (@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.ixxuVoZ8qJT7SLKn]{[39] Villein (Arge of Clan Kralis)}) the clan head. Her husband was killed trying to protect her from wolves, with a garden hoe as his only weapon, when she was attacked while working in their garden plot last winter. He left her with a son (13) and two daughters (15 and 14). Her brother lives with them, but he has been blind since birth. She often complains that it should have been him that died, not her beloved husband.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":7200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"GafDnQ5j88ctMsnK","name":"[A] Manor House","content":"<p>The manor house is extremely rundown. See detailed description on the following pages.</p>\n\n","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"HgD6rUwomnijjcvw","name":"[D] Peonian Shrine","content":"<h2>Peonian Shrine</h2>\n<p><img style=\"width:100%\" src=\"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/peonian-shrine.webp\" /></p>\n<p>Little more than a stack of field stone and a few donations, this shrine is typical of the Peonian shrines that dot the Kaldoric countryside.</p>","img":"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/peonian-shrine.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":800000},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"KLtkHM53bBjkxI2S","name":"[32] Cottar-Beadle (Kloril of Clan Ibin)","content":"<p>The role of beadle is that of village policeman and enforcer of the lord’s will. Never has someone relished his task as much as Kloril. A single man with a large red birthmark on his face, Kloril was tormented all his life. Akitt recognised this and used it to his advantag putting Kloril in charge of those who had tormented him as a child. As a single man (his parents died years ago), he had no ties to any of the other clans. He now fears for his life. He has been very quiet since Akitt fled.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":6400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"KuP9TvinoUxnsBh9","name":"[M5] Stables","content":"<h2>Stables</h2><p>Until recently, this shed housed the four horses and three mules that belonging to Lord Akitt. It is in reasonable shape, though the floor has a thick layer of manure and is quite muddy. One poor stable boy lives in the loft. When Lord Akitt fired the ostler, he was left to tend all of the horses and mules, clean the tack and muck out the stables, an impossible task for a 13 year old boy. He was frequently beaten by the recently departed bailiff and cringes at the approach of any important looking person. He is starved for affection and will latch on to the first person who is nice to him.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"MJ2MKr5Zqeg2avLL","name":"[25] Half-Villein (Ithar of Clan Kralis)","content":"<p>More than any other family, Ithar’s family suffered at the hand of Lord Akitt. On returning from a days work in the forest, he came across Hedin (one of Akitt’s mercenaries) raping his daughter. His son had already tried to come to her aid, but had been killed by Hedin and lay dead in the road, while his daughter screamed. When Ithar raised his axe to attack Hedin, the other mercenary, Kenric, took his arm off at the shoulder with one stroke of his sword. Akitt allowed Ithar to live and put his son’s head on a pike as a warning to the other villagers. Ithar’s wife struggles to support her one-armed husband and her traumatized daughter.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":5000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"MoKlNWRylxzuwJQE","name":"[2] Villein (Eld of Clan Kralis)","content":"<p>A member of the second largest clan, Eld is squeaking by through careful management of his twenty-two acres. Only his wife and his brother survived out of a family of seven. He lost his parents and two children to starvation in the winter of 717. Their deaths mean the survivors have enough to eat most days.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
