{"_id":"VB5J5hr2AZLW5v2t","name":"[M6] Barn","content":"<h2>Barn</h2><p>Used as a granary, the barn is over thirty years old. Clan Morfan had planned to replace it in 716TR, but it was never done. The barn has a very distinct lean to one side as a result of weakening timbers. There is no foundation to speak of and the timbers were set directly in the ground causing them to rot badly. The barn is moderately full of goods that Akitt extorted from the villagers and didn’t have time to sell. With careful management, they might get the village through to the next harvest.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Vr0Ph882teu5FxDo","name":"[28] Cottar (Aslen of Clan Torlis)","content":"<p>Aslen was never married. The only reason he has not fled is because of the retribution that would be visited upon his mother and brother (@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.gp7NYpWAdBb5JCXj]{[20] Cottar (Arsain of Clan Torlis)}). He and the timberwright’s apprentice, Thales, are lovers. Most of the villagers know but don’t care as long as they are discreet.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":5600000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
