{"_id":"qNxgZjixnptvBkeT","name":"[M1] Causeway","content":"<h2>Causeway</h2><p>The manor originally had a wooden bridge leading to a gate. When the previous bailiff’s hunted out all the wolves in the local area, they filled in part of the moat and removed the gate and a portion of wall to ease access to the barn and manor house in anticipation of major construction work.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_dn7blwley0v","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"rmX7nKyb5JQrRq5L","name":"[T5] Sawdust Pile","content":"<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">Each day, the sawdust from the pit had to be dug out and piled into this bin. Lynd then sold the sawdust to tanners for the tannic acid. Nothing that could make him a profit was wasted. He even had a monopoly on firewood, forcing the villagers to buy the wood they themselves had felled, cut and piled.</span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZHcuaOyz810x9hQU":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.mQ1rIs2x1sivFXGl"},"cf":{"id":"temp_frexav32o9u","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"rqNEKzRTdp8wiP6i","name":"[J] Demesne Farm","content":"<h2>Demesne Farm</h2><p>These building compose the working out-buildings of the Lord’s farm, including the cow barn, pig sty and sheep shed. The buildings are well constructed and though neglected and dirty are still in good shape. The Reeve supervises all work here.</p>\n","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":2000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"syPVhIApaqPQmOgW","name":"[14] Villein-Woodward (Muir of Clan Torlis)","content":"<p>Since he was thrown out the front door of the manor hall, Muir has taken a very liberal attitude to his duties. If he is not allowed to regulate the timberwright then why should he regulate the villagers? Poaching is rampant, Muir being among the worst offenders. The deer he shoots have kept more than one member of Clan Torlis from starving to death these last five years. Akitt did not hunt, so he didn’t notice. Muir’s wife and three sons are among the best fed in the village. Even so, Muir is careful to be generous with any surplus from his thirty-nine acres to stay on the good side of the other villagers.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":2800000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"trNFqgeEGoXbgoUR","name":"[T4] Sawpit","content":"<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">The large pit in the middle of the yard is used to cut logs into timbers. Trees are felled in the forest and any branches trimmed off for sale as wattle material or firewood. The logs are then hauled to the yard, where they are stockpiled before being cut into square or rectangular beams for use in timber-frame construction. The process of sawing the logs involves one man in the pit underneath the log hauling down on the saw, while the man on the top hauls the saw back up for the next cut. The man in the pit does most of the cutting action and eats a face full of sawdust. The man on top has to haul the heavy saw up with each stroke. Both are backbreaking jobs. Lynd forced the village men to take turns while he supervised. When they were to slow, he “encouraged” them with a long ox whip. Most of the men in the village and Lynd’s apprentice bear many scars from this whip.</span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ZHcuaOyz810x9hQU":3},"flags":{"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nCdrwOOxiTVu1vQv"},"cf":{"id":"temp_frexav32o9u","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"u3EWRJLUDTxQKTGQ","name":"[15] Villein (Ulstin of Clan Heryla)","content":"<p>Ulstin, his wife, father and two aunts, have survived the famine and hardship with some grace. Although only a mediocre farmer, he has thirty-two acres, enough to support his family. His father can still work and his wife is strong, so they work the family land while he cuts trees. His three daughters died of the cough because of a lack of firewood for heating.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":3000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"uVp8CozVEh2arjHr","name":"[18] Cottar (Witol of Clan Sarion)","content":"<p>Witol is the former reeve of Charmic. As stated in The Dark Years above, he was stripped of his office and his son was killed for trying to runaway in 717. Witol is a broken man, but if his confidence can be restored, he is the one man who could bring some order to the village and start to rebuild the manor and his own life.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":3600000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"uvrpyiav8Ifxns6A","name":"[22] Villein (Col of Clan Drebor)","content":"<p>Because of their size and strength, Col and his two sons were regularly conscripted to saw beams at the timberwright’s yard. After a punishing day, they would spend half the night in the fields trying to keep food on the table. They succeeded, but at the cost of Col’s health. He took to his bed with a racking cough two weeks ago. He won’t live out the month.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":4400000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"v27HZgZo5lrPxZar","name":"[5] Half-Villein (Barane of Clan Heryla)","content":"<p>Despite Akitt’s departure, Barane will not live out the month. His wife and two teenage sons have been frantic since he broke his leg plowing three weeks ago. The wound has turned septic and he will die shortly. Barane is trying to make his wife promise not to turn out his two worthless sisters when he dies, but her mind is set, without her husband, her children come first. No matter what happens, the two former domestics will be homeless within the month.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":1000000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"w2K6gQyVJHXFb6To","name":"[I] Timberwright's Yard","content":"<h1>Timberwright’s Yard</h1>\n<p><img style=\"width:100%\" src=\"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/timberwrights-yard.webp\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">The yard includes the finest house in the village. Until Lynd left, it was the hub of activity in the village. Now it is eerily quiet. The temporary bailiff is currently staying here.</span></p>\n<p>Lynd’s yard is in the centre of the village. The site was chosen for its easy access for wagons and to get the maximum work out of the serfs. Some of the wood came from the Charmic Manor wood lot, but most of it came from the King’s forest outside the manor boundaries. The villagers hopes that the King’s Forester would find out and put and end to Lynd and Akitt were dashed when they saw the man accept a large bribe from the cousins and ride away with a big smile on his face (GM Note: The Earl will want to know this and definitely bring it to the attention of the King. This may lead to a second search…for the Forester.).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.m2FprhjCX1XAG2Cq]{Tool Shed}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.xgZPCm7hGQ4YKzG2]{Timberwright’s House}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[hm-loc-charmic.journals.hUrOCmU9nQFTp7V9]{Drying House}</li>\n</ul>\n","img":"modules/hm-loc-charmic/assets/images/timberwrights-yard.webp","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":0},"cf":{"id":"temp_7b68j8e8k4","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"w40jwHFRqfGEGrIn","name":"[21] Miller (Deren of Clan Kleve)","content":"<p>Size: 2 Quality: ★★★ Price: Average</p>\n<p>With Lord Akitt’s departure, Deren is packing up his family (wife, son, niece and apprentice) and going while the going is good. He has already contacted his brother (and fellow miller) near Kiban and plans to move there within the month. Only quick action will convince him to stay.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PusKspNsRtwjEZQs":3},"flags":{"entityorder":{"order":4200000},"cf":{"id":"temp_vp55g1baur9","color":"#000000"}}}
